==English==
===Etymology===
Greek [[κακοδαιμων]] ‘evil genius’, from [[κακος]] ‘bad’ + [[δαιμων]] ‘genius, divinity’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/kækə'di:mən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|cacodemon|cacodemons}}
# an evil or [[malevolent]] spirit

